plot: While attempting to evade the rebels, Joel and Ellie cross paths with the most wanted man in Kansas City. Kathleen continues her hunt.

On the streets of a newly free Kansas City, Henry fights to protect his brother Sam from rebel soldiers who will stop at nothing to appease their ruthless leader. As her manhunt continues, Kathleen doubles down on her quest for revenge, while Ellie forms a meaningful friendship.—HBO

After the tense encounter, Joel and Henry team-up while Ellie and Sam get along. Nick learns that Henry is a collaborator that betrayed Kathleen's brother to get medicine from the FEDRA for his son. They plan to flee from Kansas City during the night, crossing the limits using the underground tunnels of sewage. They succeed, but stumble upon a sniper of the resistance that holds them until the militia comes. Out of the blue, something happens in the underground.—Claudio Carvalho, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil
